data.description: Buyer Back Out For No Reason. Back on the Market. Beautiful three-bedroom home on a neighborhood street in the city. Two of the most important main concerns are taken care of: the roof is four years old, and the furnace is two years old. The kitchen floor was also just recently redone, as well as the decking on the front porch. The home's main floor has a cozy living room and a formal dining room with sliding glass doors onto the deck for dining al fresco. The deck overlooks the extra lot which is great for a family with room to play catch, a firepit to enjoy the summer/fall evenings, or just hang out and relax. The kitchen is thoughtfully laid out with updated countertops and workspace lighting. The first floor also has a half-bath and a laundry. The three bedrooms are on the second floor, and all have a ceiling fan and closet space. The full bathroom is on the second floor, and the flooring has been updated. There is stair access to the finished attic through the Buffalo Bills bedroom. The attic could be used as a playroom or hobby space.  The home has a 1-car garage, and the driveway is shared. The sale is contingent on the Seller closing on the house she has under contract.
